76561197975607244,Recommended,255300,31274600,Posted: 21 April,all,Nomad,"This is a point and click adventure about Roaches. The name probably gave that away. It is a fun little game, a little on the short side. The humour is great,  although it ventures into the slightly lewd at times, The fun characters and puzzles are accompanied by the undertone of the world having gone through nuclear holocaust. Nothing beats Nuclear Holocaust in giving a game a dark tone. That said the game still manages to be relatively jovial and light-hearted.The story follows two friends trying to make it in a world now ruled by militant ants. With the help of a few friends along the way they battle against the military might of ants. I thoroughly enjoyed this game. Again it was a bit short but the puzzles were varied and interesting. The characters are conveyed through their interactions as no dialogue is used. Speech/thought bubbles are used throughout to help characterize and indicate what you need to do to progress. It is really well done. The graphics and art style fit the game. Also the sounds are excellent, there is no voice acting as such but you get a real feel for the characters from the sounds, screams, etc. that they do make. The""cut scenes"" come in the form of animated ""comic panels"" another style choice of which I approve.If you are a fan of this kind of game I would pick this up."
