76561198063236340,Recommended,255300,23851546,"Posted: 26 June, 2016",all,Enshammon,"4 / 5 starsBottom Line: This game is a great combination of originality, puzzle solving, surprising humor, endearing artwork, and brevity.You will enjoy this game if you are looking for:A different kind of gameA short gameThe adventure-puzzle genreA chance to support indie developersJourney of a Roach was a game I gambled on and won. I saw it come up as a Steam advertisement, and after having seen a dozen or more “stupid” games being advertised, something in me decided to check out one of them. I picked this up for a few dollars, and it sat unplayed for most of a year.By the time I dusted it off last week, I was pleased to find that it was exactly what I was looking for. Simply put, it is an adventure-puzzle game with a very simple and intuitive interface, and yes, you are a roach.I enjoyed almost every aspect of the game. I laughed, felt sad, smiled, and felt my eyes go wide on a few occasions throughout. It is a short game, but that is something I count as an advantage. I feel that I got everything I wanted out of it and did not waste time on repetitive content.Journey of a Roach is a single-player game, but in retrospect, it would have been fun to sit down with a friend and figure out the puzzles together. For the most part, though, I think it is perfectly great in solitaire.There were a few things that distracted from the fun of Roach. The first thing I encountered was the music. Early in the game, the music is so terrible that it was making me sick. There were bendy, modulated, sickly notes during one puzzle, so I turned it off. By the end, the music was better, but I did not listen to it most of the game just in case.Second, as with any puzzle game, it is very hard to get all of the clues fall within the perfect range of difficulty for a wide range of players. Journey of a Roach did a good job; in fact, most of the time, I realized later that there were subtle clues I missed. Nevertheless, there were a couple of times where I felt quite frustrated. Once, I looked it up after having spent thirty minutes on a single part of a puzzle, and it turned out that an idea I had thought might work but did not realize was actually doable (negative metagame thinking) was the right thing. In the end, this is a minor negative: that things that should be doable are not while others you might not expect are.Third, and this may be the biggest negative for me, the camera follows your perspective at all times. Oh, and you are a roach, remember? I am no entomologist, but it appears roaches can walk on walls and ceilings. If you are even remotely prone to motion sickness, …holy roaches, buckle up. I learned to squint, look away, or lay my head back while exploring certain parts of the game.All things considered, Journey of a Roach is a great game that does exactly what it sets out to do. If you are thinking about it, just buy it and have some fun."
