76561197960931103,Recommended,255300,30451495,Posted: 11 March,all,caruch2001,"This is a short yet fun point and click adventure game. Playing as a roach allows you to climb on walls and even go upside down. This is the main mechanic of the game and is used heavily to progress through and solve puzzles. The puzzles themselves can be tricky but definitely doable.Graphics and sound wise it’s very charming. The world is fairly detailed and everything was very sharp even at 1440p. Different rooms may have different music or ambient noise. It all works well together. The cutscenes are animated in a cartoon style and are fun to watch. There is no text and no verbal communication. You rely on small picture hints when clicking or hovering over hot spots to understand what is going on.The controls are simply and intuitive. I played with a keyboard and mouse. One great control idea was to put the scroll wheel as one of the actions to bring down your inventory screen. It’s very natural to scroll down in order to…well…scroll down the inventory. I don’t remember that being in other point and click games, so it was a nice addition.Pros+60FPS+Cute characters & “voices”+Controls+Music+Art style & graphics+Fun and sometimes head scratching puzzlesCons+Short!My only wish is that the game was longer. It’ll only take 2-3 hours depending on how quickly you solve the puzzles. There is even a speed runner achievement for <18 minutes, if that tell you anything!A very well done game but the asking price of $15 is too much. Be sure to grab this on sale, you won’t be disappointed.7/10Good"
