76561198095041903,Recommended,255300,34701254,Posted: 2 September,all,Charles Pendragon,"This is a case where I wish the had a mixed option for reviews, cause that's what I feel about this game. Most everything works fine, no bugs (well, not performance wise) or problems to speak of, controls operate fine for an adventure game, though there are some cases where changing crawling on wolls can get annoying, though not enough to really be a problem.The story is pretty minimal, Two roach friends go to find a flower (a rarity in a post-apocalyptic earth) and end up in a long misadventure due to the roach Bud's incredible bad luck, so his friend (the one you play as) has to save him, multiple times. Not much more than that without going into specifics, but it's a nice story.That gameplay is where I feel less than entertained. My main problem is that, for a few of the puzzles, there isn't much to go on and the vagueness of the explanation for the puzzles and items can make the puzzles less than clear, for instance. and spoilersAt the end of the game, you need to find a replacement for a button for a crane operating machine, there's a mushroom item that, when clicked on, shows a image telling you its a toxic, psychedelic mushroom, so you might think, ""Hmmm, do I have to try feeding it someone to make them do something, or distract them?"" But no, it's the button you need, and completely illogical given the nature of the machine as the buttons are not mechanical, but electrical.There's only a few other's like this (though for different reasons), but overall the puzzles feel sensible. I only had to look up answers three times. There is however an issue I take with arbitrarily limiting the player's movelent solely to make puzzles operate a certain way. You can only walk on select walls and objects to the left an right, but not everything, and walls on the background or foreground are completey unscalable. It's not technically problematic, but logically, it feels lazy. They could have at least given resoning to this.Besides that, to me, neither the story nor gameplay were too interesting or engaging to really be fun for me. An okay game with some overly vague puzzles, hence the mixed opinion, but I'll give it a thumbs up since it is done well overall.Also, it may say I only played a few minutes, but that's only cause I played on offline mode.Edit: Forgot to mention, as other's have said, I would not recommend this game at full price. I got it for 1$ U.S., and that feels about a fair price given the content, length, and replayability."
